Done. `transcript.json` (25 iterations, 130 hypotheses, 130 analyses, schema-validated) and `analysis_summary.txt` (~324 lines, narrative + per-iteration findings + 11-point synthesis) are written in the bundle directory.

Key findings the data actually supported:
- **Palbociclib × ER+** is the only robust drug-biomarker interaction (~+1.58 mo PFS, p≈0), holding up under full adjustment.
- **Olaparib × BRCA** is borderline (+0.40 mo, p=0.02 crude; ns after adjustment).
- The other canonical pairings (trastuzumab/HER2+, tamoxifen/ER+, sacituzumab/HER2-low, pembrolizumab/MSI-high) show no detectable interaction.
- Disease burden (stage IV, brain mets, ECOG) and intrinsic biology (ER+/PR+ positive; HER2+/PIK3CA negative) carry the bulk of prognostic information; albumin/weight loss/calcium/inflammation composite contribute modestly.
- Notable surprises: older age associates with **longer** PFS in this cohort; higher ki67 attenuates the palbociclib benefit; no demographic/access disparities detectable.
